.TH "DECREE" "1" "Jan 2026" "OpenDecree" "OpenDecree CLI"

.SH NAME
decree-migrate - Apply database migrations


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdecree migrate [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Apply the OpenDecree database schema migrations.

.PP
Migrations create the tables, row-level-security policies, and the unprivileged
"decree_app" role that the server assumes (SET ROLE) on every connection. A fresh
database must be migrated before the server can start, otherwise the server fails
with: role "decree_app" does not exist.

.PP
Connect as a role that may CREATE ROLE and GRANT — the database owner or a
superuser — not as decree_app. Running "up" repeatedly is safe; already-applied
migrations are skipped.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--db-url\fP=""
	PostgreSQL connection URL for the owner/superuser role (defaults to $DB_WRITE_URL)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for migrate


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--insecure\fP[=false]
	disable TLS (plaintext); for local development only

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	output format: table, json, yaml

.PP
\fB--role\fP="superadmin"
	actor role (x-role header)

.PP
\fB--server\fP="localhost:9090"
	gRPC server address

.PP
\fB--subject\fP=""
	actor identity (x-subject header)

.PP
\fB--tenant-id\fP=""
	auth tenant ID (x-tenant-id header)

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	JWT bearer token (prefer DECREE_TOKEN env var to avoid shell history exposure)

.PP
\fB--token-file\fP=""
	path to a file containing the JWT bearer token (takes precedence over --token)

.PP
\fB--wait\fP[=false]
	wait for the server to be ready before executing the command

.PP
\fB--wait-timeout\fP="60s"
	maximum time to wait for server readiness


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdecree(1)\fP, \fBdecree-migrate-down(1)\fP, \fBdecree-migrate-status(1)\fP, \fBdecree-migrate-up(1)\fP
